  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">13 quarry mining companies have been mining black granite in Mutoko for the last 3 decades. These mining activities have caused severe environmental degradation. It has reduced the amount of arable, pasture and sacred lands because they are being used as dumping sites; it has caused health problems caused by the dust created by trucks; and has forcefully displaces families without compensation. MNCDT would like to conduct a six month project to raise awareness about the environmental impacts of black granite mining and to monitor and document cases of environmental degradation. Specifically, MNCDT would like to use the grant to purchase two cameras and two phones for environmental monitoring; to produce three environmental degradation and community rights monitoring reports; to hold three training meetings; and to establish two environmental youth groups in 2 schools.</narrative>
  </description>
